      <description>&lt;p&gt;â†’ &lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_zh/discover/&#34;&gt;Chinese Version&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://www.paulgraham.com/discover.html&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://www.paulgraham.com/discover.html&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://www.paulgraham.com/discover.html&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;persuade-xor-discover&#34;&gt;Persuade xor Discover&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;September 2009&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When meeting people you don&amp;rsquo;t know very well, the convention is to seem extra friendly. You smile and say &amp;ldquo;pleased to meet you,&amp;rdquo; whether you are or not. There&amp;rsquo;s nothing dishonest about this. Everyone knows that these little social lies aren&amp;rsquo;t meant to be taken literally, just as everyone knows that &amp;ldquo;Can you pass the salt?&amp;rdquo; is only grammatically a question.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
